  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (56dc746 2022-08-26T00:04:23.353510521Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test \n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHi, I found this bug while using fore test to reproduce an hack.\r\n```solidity\r\nforkId = vm.createFork(url, 14595905);\r\nvm.selectFork(forkId);\r\nvm.startBroadcast(0x1c5dCdd006EA78a7E4783f9e6021C32935a10fb4);\r\nbeanexp = new BeanExploit();\r\n```\r\nThere is two step for my work, the first step is in block hight 14595905, this step worked successfully.\r\nThe second step is in block hight 14602789, I use vm.rollfork() to change block number.\r\n```solidity\r\nvm.rollFork(14602789);\r\n// some change chain status codes\r\n```\r\nUnfortunately, it doesn't work properly. And forge test throw `EvmError: Revert`.\r\nAnd I change my code to just query chain data. It can works successfully.\r\n```solidity\r\nvm.rollFork(14602789);\r\nuint112 r1;\r\n(,r1, )= IUniswapV2Pair(0x87898263B6C5BABe34b4ec53F22d98430b91e371).getReserves();\r\nconsole.log(r1);\r\n```\r\nDue to the error message is simpler, it is difficult for me to find the cause of the error.\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n",
